  "description": "Phase-14 successor to Phase-13. Six corpora (M77, permuted-M77, Linear B, Sanskrit, Luwian, Sumerian) each profiled by Block Entropy + Zipf-Mandelbrot + MI Decay + HED + Epistatic Interaction. Profiles ranked by LanguageSignatureComparator vs natural-language template + permuted negative-control template. Three corpora's DoF vectors projected through the language_signature CAS-YAML via CPSC IterativeEngine for deterministic max_violation. ICIT metadata + SignContextAssociation + DerivedAnchorSet measures whether Indus signs are externally grounded by site / artifact-type / direction / length-bin. EpistaticAnchorRanker ranks M77 signs by epistatic centrality (information-theoretic anchor selection). LanguageDetectorVerdict integrates all signature tests into a yes/no/maybe answer to 'is Indus a real language?' Result is reports/indus_phase14_full.json.",
